# Appointment Page Logic Fixes

5 targeted fixes across 4 files.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Double-Booking → Reschedule Wording

#### [MODIFY] [create_appointment_screen.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/appointments/screens/create_appointment_screen.dart)

- **Line 176**: Change `"Do you want to replace it with a new one?"` → `"Do you want to reschedule the appointment to this slot?"`
- **Line 183**: Change button text `"Replace"` → `"Reschedule"`
- **Line 195**: Change snackbar text → `"Keeping the existing appointment."`

---

### 2. Future Cards → Reschedule Button + Today Cards → Patient Arrived

#### [MODIFY] [appointment_list_screen.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/appointments/screens/appointment_list_screen.dart)

**Logic change in [_ScheduleCard](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/appointments/screens/appointment_list_screen.dart#482-507) (line 573-581):**
- Add a `isFutureDate` boolean check comparing `apt.date` to today's date
- `showArrivedBtn` = scheduled AND today AND not walk-in (as before, but restricted to today)
- New `showRescheduleBtn` = scheduled AND future date
- Reschedule button opens the [AvailableSlotsScreen](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/scheduling/screens/available_slots_screen.dart#12-36), and on slot selection, updates the appointment's date/time and deletes the old one

**New `_rescheduleAppointment` method in the parent state class:**
- Opens [AvailableSlotsScreen](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/scheduling/screens/available_slots_screen.dart#12-36) the same way as create appointment
- On slot selection: calls a new `rescheduleAppointment` service method to update date + time
- Refreshes the appointment list

#### [MODIFY] [appointment_service.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/core/services/appointment_service.dart)

- Add `rescheduleAppointment(id, newDate, newTime)` — updates the appointment record's [date](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/appointments/providers/appointment_provider.dart#191-200) and `time` fields

---

### 3. Arrived Time = Non-Clickable Info + Undo Button

#### [MODIFY] [appointment_list_screen.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/appointments/screens/appointment_list_screen.dart)

**Fix the tap behavior (line 173-183 [_navigateToPatient](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/appointments/screens/appointment_list_screen.dart#173-200)):**
- Remove the "Patient hasn't arrived yet" snackbar when tapping a card without a linked patient
- Instead, do nothing (or show nothing) — the card's arrived info is purely informational

**Fix the check-in time row (line 703-717):**
- Already just a [Row](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/patients/screens/patient_profile_screen.dart#196-209) inside a `Padding` — it is non-clickable by itself, but the parent `GestureDetector` wraps the whole card with `onTap: widget.onTap` which triggers [_navigateToPatient](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/appointments/screens/appointment_list_screen.dart#173-200)
- The fix: make [_navigateToPatient](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/appointments/screens/appointment_list_screen.dart#173-200) return early gracefully (no snackbar) if patient hasn't arrived, OR check if status is `inProgress` and patientId is empty (fill details first)

**Add "Undo Arrived" option:**
- When `apt.status == inProgress` and check-in time is shown, add a small "Undo" text button next to the arrived time
- `_undoArrived` method: calls a new `undoArrived(id)` service method that resets status to `scheduled` and clears `check_in_time`

#### [MODIFY] [appointment_service.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/core/services/appointment_service.dart)

- Add `undoArrived(appointmentId)` — sets status back to `scheduled` and clears `check_in_time`

---

### 4. Missed Appointment Indicator (Past Day No-Show)

#### [MODIFY] [appointment_list_screen.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/appointments/screens/appointment_list_screen.dart)

**New `_isMissed` method:**
- Returns true if: `apt.status == scheduled` AND `apt.date` is before today
- These are past-day appointments where the patient never arrived

**Card styling for missed:**
- Show a red "Missed" status pill instead of "Scheduled"
- Disable action buttons for missed cards
- Add a subtle strikethrough or grayed-out visual

---

### 5. DoB Format: DD/MM/YYYY + Auto-Separator

#### [MODIFY] [patient_info_screen.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/appointments/screens/patient_info_screen.dart)

- **Line 71-72**: Change format from `YYYY-MM-DD` → `DD/MM/YYYY`
- **Line 235**: Change hint from `'YYYY-MM-DD'` → `'DD/MM/YYYY'`
- **Line 228-237**: Remove `AbsorbPointer` wrapper, allow manual typing
- Add a custom `TextInputFormatter` that auto-inserts `/` after DD and MM
- Keep the calendar picker as an alternative (tap on calendar icon)

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
- Hot reload the app
- Test call-by booking with same phone → check reschedule wording
- Test future date cards → check reschedule button appears
- Test today cards → check Patient Arrived button
- Test tapping arrived time → no snackbar, just info
- Test undo arrived → status reverts
- Navigate to a past date with scheduled appts → check Missed indicator
- Test DoB field → auto `/` insertion and DD/MM/YYYY format
